{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/text-data-augmentation-f4143571ecd2", "time": 1683012399.426878, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/text-data-augmentation-f4143571ecd2/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Text Data Augmentation. A brief introduction to TextAttack and\u2026 | by Chetan Ambi | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Text Data Augmentation", "description": "Data Augmentation is the process that enables us to increase the size of the training data without actually collecting the data. But why do we need more data? The answer is simple \u2014 the more data we\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://simonsinek.com/about/", "anchor_text": "Simon Sinek", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://github.com/QData/TextAttack", "anchor_text": "TextAttack", "paragraph_index": 6}, {"url": "https://github.com/QData/TextAttack#augmenting-text-textattack-augment", "anchor_text": "official documentation", "paragraph_index": 7}, {"url": "https://translate.google.com/", "anchor_text": "Google Translate Ajax API", "paragraph_index": 10}, {"url": "https://pythonsimplified.com/home/", "anchor_text": "subscribe", "paragraph_index": 17}, {"url": "http://www.pythonsimplified.com/", "anchor_text": "www.pythonsimplified.com", "paragraph_index": 17}, {"url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/chetanambi/", "anchor_text": "LinkedIn", "paragraph_index": 17}, {"url": "https://pythonsimplified.com/", "anchor_text": "https://pythonsimplified.com/", "paragraph_index": 19}], "all_paragraphs": ["Data Augmentation is the process that enables us to increase the size of the training data without actually collecting the data. But why do we need more data? The answer is simple \u2014 the more data we have, the better the performance of the model.", "Image data augmentation steps such as flipping, cropping, rotation, blurring, zooming, etc. helped tremendously in computer vision. Also, it is relatively easy to create augmented images but the same is not the case with Natural Language Processing (NLP) due to the complexities inherent in the language. (For example, we can not replace every word by its synonym, and even if we replace it, the meaning of the sentence might change completely). Based on my findings/research, I haven\u2019t seen as much research around text data augmentation as image augmentation.", "However, in this article, we will go thru 2 libraries TextAttack & Googletrans I have come across recently when I was trying augmentation for text data. So, let\u2019s get started.", "We will apply the augmentation techniques we are going to learn on these quotes of Simon Sinek.", "\u201cLeadership requires two things: a vision of the world that does not yet exist and the ability to communicate it.\u201d", "\u201cThe role of a leader is not to come up with all the great ideas. The role of a leader is to create an environment in which great ideas can happen\u201d", "TextAttack is a Python framework for adversarial attacks, adversarial training, and data augmentation in NLP. In this article, we will focus only on data augmentation.", "The textattack.Augmenter class provides six methods for data augmentation. You can find the detailed description of these methods in the official documentation.", "Let\u2019s look at the data augmentation results using these four methods. Note that pct_words_to_swap=0.1, transformations_per_example=4 are passed to each of these methods by default. We can modify these default values as needed.", "We can apply these methods to real-world data to increase the size of the data. The sample code is given below. Here the originaltrain dataframe is copied to the train_aug dataframe and then augmentation is applied on train_aug. And finally, train_aug is appended to the original train dataset.", "Googletrans is built on top of Google Translate API. This uses Google Translate Ajax API for language detection and translation.", "The key parameters to translate() method are:", "src: source language. Optional parameter as googletrans will detect it.", "text: the text to be translated from source language to the destination language. Mandatory parameter.", "As we can see, the given text is first translated from English to Italian and then translated to back to English. During this back translation, as we can see, there is a slight change in the sentence between the original text and the back-translated text but the overall meaning of the sentence is still retained.", "We can apply this technique to real-world data. The sample code is given below. Here the original train dataframe is copied to tran_aug dataframe and then back-translation is applied on train_aug dataframe. And finally, train_aug is appended to the original train dataframe. Note that we are translating original text from English to Italian and then from Italian to English.", "Now you know how to make use of TextAttack and Googletrans libraries for your data science projects for text data augmentation.", "To read more such interesting articles on Python and Data Science, subscribe to my blog www.pythonsimplified.com. You can also reach me on LinkedIn.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Data Science | Machine Learning | Python. Visit https://pythonsimplified.com/ for interesting articles on Python and Machine Learning ."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Ff4143571ecd2&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Ftext-data-augmentation-f4143571ecd2&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Ftext-data-augmentation-f4143571e